    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in Traffic Flow Template packet filter encoding\n\n### Summary\nThe Traffic Flow Template encoding functions were missing proper buffer length validation, which could lead to buffer overflows when encoding packet filter identifiers. This issue manifests as memory corruption during NAS message encoding when processing TFT operations with DELETE_PACKET opcodes.\n\nThe fix adds proper buffer validation checks to prevent out-of-bounds memory writes.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/TrafficFlowTemplate.c`: Added buffer validation in `encode_traffic_flow_template_packet_filter_identifiers` and fixed incorrect error code usage in `encode_traffic_flow_template_packet_filters`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Create a Traffic Flow Template with DELETE_PACKET operation code\n2. Provide a buffer that is smaller than required for the number of packet filters\n3. Call `encode_traffic_flow_template` \n4. Observe buffer overflow and potential memory corruption\n\nThe issue can also be triggered by passing NULL buffer pointers, which previously would cause segmentation faults.\n"
}